files.description: R code to replicate every model and figure presented in the paper. The code progresses from estimating propensity to take a hostile immigration stance to a model of the Republican share of the two-party vote. The code is written to use election2010_2.csv as the data file.

files.description: ZIP archive of every 2010 House Republican candidate's position on immigration, taken from the candidate's website. Each statement is in a separate plain text file. File names are based on the candidate's state and district. (E.g., "al2.txt" gives the statement for the Republican from Alabama's second district.) Blank files indicate that no statement could be found.
files.label: immigStatements.zip
